Rotax 914 Turbo powerplant offers more performance at high altitudes with a lower weight engine. TBO=2000 hrs., automatic waste gate control, altitude compensating mixture (no red lever required) and dual electronic ignition.

ROTAX 912 offers low operating costs along with your choice of MOGAS or AVGAS. 4-cylinder 4-stroke liquid-/air-cooled engine with opposed cylinders Dry sump forced lubrication with separate oil tank, automatic adjustment by hydraulic valve tappet Mechanical fuel pump Dual electronic ignition Propeller speed reduction unit Air intake system Gearbox Reduction Ratio 2,43:1 The turbo charged ROTAX 914 offers more performance at high altitudes while delivering lower weight engines. 115 hp, TBO = 2,000 hrs. Automatic waste gate control Automatic adjustment by hydraulic valve tappet 2 carburetors Dual electronic ignition

The P2008 LSA offers engine choices to suit your mission: Rotax 912 ULS engine: delivers significantly better fuel efficiency and lower operating costs than comparable light sport and ultra-light aircraft. Regional Airport (ENW). The first flight took place at ENW on 12-9-1984. After the annual inspection in 1999 by the FBO at ENW the FBO did not tie down the Tail before the FBO did their after inspection engine run-up. The tail lifted and the prop struck the ground. The engine was removed and was taken to G&N Aviation in Griffith, Indiana. The engine was disassembled and inspected. The engine was reassembled using new slick mags, new Lamar starter, rebuilt prop governor from Hartzell, new rod and main bearings, new oil pump gears, all new hardware and other miscellaneous parts. The engine was painted red and dynoed. The engine was installed on the Thorp with new Lord mounts and bolts. At this time a new Hartzell constant speed prop was installed. O RV-10 foi desenvolvido para voar com vrias verses do consagrado motor seis cilindros Lycoming XI0-540 que desenvolve 260 hp. Quando pilotos dizem performance isso realmente quer dizer velocidade. O RV-10 to estvel quanto rpido, voc poder cruzar a at 205mph (330 km/h) com a mxima segurana e tranquilidade, mas essa s e uma das caracterticas do RV-10, cruzando em velocidade de cruzeiro econmico em torno de 50-55% de potncia no motor com velocidades em torno de 175 mph sero atingidas, fazendo o custo de Km/l voado ficar abaixo da maioria dos carros de luxo.

A simplicidade se une sofisticao no painel de vo G3X. Combinando uma arquitetura flexvel com uma interface similar ao G1000, o GDU pode realizar diversas tarefas simultneas e possui uma tela grande WVGA de alta definio de 7 polegadas, receptor GPS de alta sensibilidade, controle de cursor joystick giratrio para entrada de dados, entrada de energia redundante e teclas de funo para seleo de modo. H um slot frontal para carto SD, facilitando a atualizao de softwares e bancos de dados. Alm disso, um mapa base aeronutico interno ajuda a fornecer referncias visuais realistas identificando cidades, estradas, rios, lagos e outras caractersticas do terreno em sua rota de vo. Voc pode escolher entre os modos de mapa VFR topogrfico e IFR de estilo de pista de vo. E para uma maior segurana em rota, voc dispe de um banco de dados interno de elevao de terreno que usa um cdigo de cores para alert-lo da proximidade de um terreno potencialmente perigoso. As visualizaes de perfil vertical e superior desses dados so apresentadas graficamente na pgina do terreno. ENGINE: LYCOMING 0-360 AID, 180 hp, S/N L-1791-36.PROPELLER: Hartzell Constant Speed, Model HC-F2YR-IF, S/N CM12223BThe Thorp has always been and is now kept in a heated hangar at the Kenosha, Wisc. Regional Airport (ENW). The first flight took place at ENW on 12-9-1984. After the annual inspection in 1999 by the FBO at ENW the FBO did not tie down the Tail before the FBO did their after inspection engine run-up. The tail lifted and the prop struck the ground. The engine was removed and was taken to G&N Aviation in Griffith, Indiana. The engine was disassembled and inspected. The engine was reassembled using new slick mags, new Lamar starter, rebuilt prop governor from Hartzell, new rod and main bearings, new oil pump gears, all new hardware and other miscellaneous parts. The engine was painted red and dynoed. The engine was installed on the Thorp with new Lord mounts and bolts. At this time a new Hartzell constant speed prop was installed. ENGINE: LYCOMING 0-360 AID, 180 hp, S/N L-1791-36.PROPELLER: Hartzell Constant Speed, Model HC-F2YR-IF, S/N CM12223BThe Thorp has always been and is now kept in a heated hangar at the Kenosha, Wisc. Regional Airport (ENW). The first flight took place at ENW on 12-9-1984. After the annual inspection in 1999 by the FBO at ENW the FBO did not tie down the Tail before the FBO did their after inspection engine run-up. The tail lifted and the prop struck the ground. The engine was removed and was taken to G&N Aviation in Griffith, Indiana. The engine was disassembled and inspected. The engine was reassembled using new slick mags, new Lamar starter, rebuilt prop governor from Hartzell, new rod and main bearings, new oil pump gears, all new hardware and other miscellaneous parts. The engine was painted red and dynoed. The engine was installed on the Thorp with new Lord mounts and bolts. At this time a new Hartzell constant speed prop was installed. Total time on the Airframe was 398.0 hrs. at this time.1. Total Time 694.4 hours airframe2. Total Time SMOH O-360 180 HP 694.4, 298.4 Since Tear Down due to prop strike3. Total Time on prop since NEW 298.4 hours4. KT76A transponder, 24 month thru 6-17-2-185. KX155 navcom6. KLX135A GPS/com7. Navaid AP-1 wing leveler, tracks GPS8. Intercom, Troll Avionics9. Electronics International Engine Analyzer, Model SR-8A, CHT/EGT all cylinders10. JPI-450 fuel scan: Gal/Hr., fuel used, fuel remaining.11. ELT, Pointer Model 3000.12. Wing Tip Strobes and Navigation Lights.13. 29 Gal. Main Fuel Tank, 16 Gal. Aux tank.14. Annual condition inspection current to 10-05-2016.15. Aerobatics permitted by the FAA operating limitations. a) Stalls, Steep turns. b) Aileron Rolls (left & right). Hammer head stall. c) Loops.16. Cruises at 195 MPH IAS at 25/2500 power setting. 17. 1034 lbs. empty weight; 1800 lbs. max gross weight.

Flightline Aviation are pleased to exclusively offer for sale this beautiful 1970 Cessna 414.
This aircraft was imported to the UK in 1987 from America. It has been meticulously looked after ever since and has had the same owner for last 32 years who has always had it hangered in the UK.
The aircraft has a brand new executive club class cabin with seating for six, a flight deck partition and a lavatory in rear. The pressurisedcabin is fully air conditioned and built for comfort with reclining seats and executive tables with drinks holders.
With added wing vortex generators and an average cruise speed of 225kts at 20,000ft this is a real touring aircraft with increased payload.
This is a fully IFR equipped machine with de-icing and certification into known icing conditions which makes it an all weather aircraft.

For further information or to arrange a viewing please contact us.

This Bombardier Global 5000 boasts a spacious 13-passenger interior, tranquil cabin tones, and a wide array of modern connectivity and entertainment options.
A classical colour scheme, comfortable seats, and a neutral veneer add to the overall tranquil atmosphere, making this Global 5000 the perfect choice for a private owner.The cabin is divided into two clubs of 4 chairs and a state room in the back that can be shut o from the remaining area with a sliding door. There are 4 single seats and a 4-seat club in the front with a dinner/conference table
The aft room features a divan that folds out into a proper bed and two more chairs.

Fifteen 15 pax VIP layout completed by PATS Aircraft 2013. With a forward
four (4) place club seating w/ pull-out tables, mid-Cabin two (2) place club
seating w/ pull-out tables opposing a three (3) place 16G berthable divan. Aft
features a four (4) place conference double club w/ Hi-Lo table, opposing two
(2) place club seating w/ pull-out tables. A pocket door separates galley from
cabin. The forward entryway has leather flight attendant jumpseat, with a
left side wardrobe and acoustical curtain. The forward galley has a pull-out
work surface, divided flatware storage drawer, Misc. storage drawers, crystal
and China storage, high temperature oven, manual fill coffee maker, insta-
hot faucet and one (1) 230V/60Hz universal outlet. The forward lavatory has
a smoke detector, dropdown oxygen mask and air gasper, hot/cold water,
vanity with storage for toiletries and waste container and a self-contained
chemical toilet. The aft lavatory has a smoke detector, dropdown oxygen
mask and air gasper, hot/cold water, attendant call switch, one (1)
230v/60hz universal outlet, pa system speaker, vanity with storage for
toiletries and waste container, external toilet service system.

The cabin is certified for 12 passengers and divided into 2 seating zones. The forward seating zone consists of 4 single chairs in a double club configuration with 2 pull out executive tables. The second zone consists of a four-place divan and a four place conference group. The plane is equipped with Lufthansa NICE cabin management system, as well as an Iridium telephone system and wireless internet.The rich palette with vibrant wooden tones and very relaxing upholstery reminds of home and helps to relax.This is a versatile aircraft for productive work or pleasant rest.

column11: North America Canada, United States - TN
column12:
ENGINES
 Top of the line Pratt & Whitney PT6A-66B push the Avanti II with 8 to 13 percent more power in cruise and climb while remaining in the basic thrust on ground. The engines also increase cruise speed and mission performances, and get up to over 402 KTAS at 31000ft with a Mmo 0.70 cruise. The PT6 is considered the most "bullet proof" turbine engine ever built and with the styling and aerodynamics of the Avanti II, you get the fastest turboprop ever built. Total Time Since Hot Section: 710 hours.

Propellers
5 bladed Hartzell HC-E5N-3A & 3AL propellers in a unique counter rotating pusher layout deliver amazing performance with a quiet cabin. Because the engine and prop are to the rear of the passengers (the props far to the rear!!) you get quiet comfort inside, with blazing speed and efficiency. Also, the props are freshly overhauled.

Collins for King Air C90GTI, S/N LJ-1889. This Bundled Solution Brings PL21-
Equipped Aircraft above Production Baseline Configuration to Maintain
the Aircraftâ€™s Viability in Nextgen Airspace. This Upgrade does not Involve
the Extensive Rework of a Full Retrofit and yet it Meets the 2020 Mandate
for ADS-B and provides SVS (Synthetic Vision) so Pilots can fly with
Increased Confidence at Night, or in any Weather. This is an Ads-B Mandate
Compliant Package which includes ADS-B out with Flight ID, Synthetic
Vision, Waas/LPV, RNP, and DBU-5010E Data Loader,
This Modernization Upgrade will Meet Current and Upcoming FAA & ICAO Changes
from Area Navigation (R-NAV) to Required Navigation Performance (RNP) and
Performance Based Navigation (PBN) Requirements.

column12:
AIRFRAME
 Corporate Concepts International, Inc. is pleased to offer this exceptional VIP Boeing 737-200 Advanced featuring 

Recent upgrades and refurbishments to interior, exterior and avionics and includes an extensive spares package.
Ultimate passenger seating comfort for 24 passengers with new generation cabin management system.
Upgrades for new flight regulations and safety including high speed Internet, CPDLC, FANS-1/A, ADS-B, Synthetic Vision and Enhanced Vision system.
Landing gear overhaul, C Inspection, and flap track inspection currently in progress Returning to service in April 2020.
Advanced, more powerful and fuel efficient JT8D-17A engines are Stage III compliant and have fresh shop visits on both engines.
Auxiliary fuel system provides 3,500 nm real world range.
This low-time B737 has never been in airline service and offers the same size and ultimate comfort as a BBJ at a fifth of the cost of the oldest BBJ.
For more details and a video of this aircraft click here B737 Video

 The JT8D-17 engines had a full shop visit in 2018.

column12: The remarkably fast Falcon 7X tri-jet is the flagship of Dassaults business jet group. Aiming for a classic yet modernaesthetic, Dassault sought BMW Group as design partner for the 7X floor-plans and interiors. The beautiful, functional and library-quiet results have been recognized with accolades from The Chicago Athenaeum and TheEuropean Centre for Architecture Art Design. Maneuverability is a critical safety feature, just ask any fighter pilot.Falcon 7X was the first business jet to use fly-by-wire technology which is normally found only in the latest airlinersand military aircraft. Dassault Falcons EASy flight deck is a revolutionary man-machine interface, whichdramatically improves situational awareness, decreases pilot workload and enhances crew coordination. Clean,reliable engines paired with precision handling capabilities. This Aircraft is operated FAR-135.

Powerplant: 3 x Lotarev D-36 turbofan engines, 63.75 kN (14,330 lbf) thrust each.

Design and development.

The engine was developed for the Yak-42, An-72 and An-74 aircraft and was very advanced when it was first introduced in the 1970s. The engine was designed by Vladimir Lotarev. The first test runs began in 1971, first flight tests followed in 1974, serial production began in 1977.

The engine has a single-stage fan with 29 titanium blades and a Kevlar outer shell, which is driven by a three-stage turbine. The six-stage low pressure compressor with titanium blades is driven by a single-stage non-cooled low pressure turbine. The seven-stage high-pressure compressor with steel blades is driven by a steel bladed high-pressure turbine.

Since the tradition in the Soviet era was to gradually and continuously improve engines in serviceability, engines went from Series 1 to 3A (depending on the application). The Series 1 (used on Yak-42D) did not feature any reverse thrust system however, series 1A to 3A were fitted with bucket-type thrust reversers (used on An-72/An-74). The most recent upgrade (after the Soviet breakup) is Series 4A which has been in manufacture since 2002. Improvements included updated curved titanium blades and a built-in reverse thrust device. More advanced blade design along with proprietary wear-resistant and heat-protective coatings have resulted in improved specific fuel consumption (kg/h/kgf) dropping from 0.65 to 0.63. Specified service life has also improved exponentially to 40,000 hours.

Powerplant: 3 x Lotarev D-36 turbofan engines, 63.75 kN (14,330 lbf) thrust each.

Design and development.

The engine was developed for the Yak-42, An-72 and An-74 aircraft and was very advanced when it was first introduced in the 1970s. The engine was designed by Vladimir Lotarev. The first test runs began in 1971, first flight tests followed in 1974, serial production began in 1977.

The engine has a single-stage fan with 29 titanium blades and a Kevlar outer shell, which is driven by a three-stage turbine. The six-stage low pressure compressor with titanium blades is driven by a single-stage non-cooled low pressure turbine. The seven-stage high-pressure compressor with steel blades is driven by a steel bladed high-pressure turbine.

Since the tradition in the Soviet era was to gradually and continuously improve engines in serviceability, engines went from Series 1 to 3A (depending on the application). The Series 1 (used on Yak-42D) did not feature any reverse thrust system however, series 1A to 3A were fitted with bucket-type thrust reversers (used on An-72/An-74). The most recent upgrade (after the Soviet breakup) is Series 4A which has been in manufacture since 2002. Improvements included updated curved titanium blades and a built-in reverse thrust device. More advanced blade design along with proprietary wear-resistant and heat-protective coatings have resulted in improved specific fuel consumption (kg/h/kgf) dropping from 0.65 to 0.63. Specified service life has also improved exponentially to 40,000 hours.

Powerplant: 3 x Ivchenko AI-25 turbofans, 14.7 kN (3,300 lbf) each
The Ivchenko AI-25 is a family of military and civilian twin-shaft medium bypass turbofan engines developed by Ivchenko OKB of the Soviet Union. It was the first bypass engine ever used on short haul aircraft in the USSR. The engine is still produced by Ukrainian based aircraft engine manufacturing company, Motor Sich.

Development

The AI-25 was designed to power the Yakovlev Yak-40 tri-jet airliner, often called the first regional jet transport aircraft, and is the starting point for the Lotarev DV-2 turbofan engine. The project was launched in 1965, with the AI-25s first test flight in 1966, and finally cleared for production in 1967. In 1972, the AI-25 was selected for the Polish PZL M-15 Belphegor, the world's only jet-powered biplane.

Development of the AI-25 continued and the uprated AI-25TL was designed for use by the Czechoslovak Aero L-39 Albatros military trainer with the first flight occurring in 1968. The L-39, would go on to become one of the most popular, and widespread trainer aircraft in the world, with over 3,000 L-39s produced, and with 2,900 examples still in active service today. A smaller version of the AI-25TL, the AI-25TLK has equipped the People's Republic of Chinas Hongdu L-11 fighter-trainer.

The AI-25TLK is also licensed built in the People's Republic of China as the WS-11. Another variant of the AI-25, is the AI-25TLSh in the 1990s, which underwent flight testing by the Ukrainian Ministry of Defense in 2002. Ivchenko-Progress is currently marketing the AI-25TLSh as an upgrade to existing L-39 and JL-8 operators that would extend the service life of the aircraft and improve performance. The latest AI-25 is the AI-25TL Series 2 designed for the Mikoyan MiG-AT.

General characteristics
Type: Turbofan
Length: 3,358 mm (132.2 in)
Diameter: ~611.6 mm (24.08 in)(intake casing)
Dry weight: 350 kg (770 lb)

Components
Compressor: Axial, 3 fan/low pressure compressor stages, 9 high pressure compressor stages
Combustors: Annular
Turbine: 1 high pressure turbine stage, 2 low pressure turbine stages
Fuel type: Aviation kerosene, JP-1 for example
Oil system: Pressure spray with return

Performance
Maximum thrust: 16.867 kN (3,792 lbf)
Overall pressure ratio: 9.5:1
Bypass ratio: 2.0:1
Fuel consumption: 468.1 kg/h (1,032 lb/h)
Specific fuel consumption: 0.58 lb/lbf/h (59 kg/kN/h)
Thrust-to-weight ratio: 4.914:1

The D-436 engine was developed as a follow on to the Lotarev D-36. The engine took several of its design features from that engine and another Progress engine, the Progress D-18. The D-436 incorporated an updated, higher RPM fan, a lower emissions combustor, and new compressor sections. Several variants of the engine incorporate a FADEC.
The "TP" variant is a specific "maritime" corrosion-resistant version developed for use in the Be-200 amphibious aircraft. This variant produces 7,500 kgf (16,534 lbf) each.
General characteristics
Type: Three-spool high bypass turbofan
Length: 3,030 mm (119 in)
Diameter: 1,390 mm (55 in)
Dry weight: 1,450 kg (3,200 lb)
Components
Compressor: Axial flow, 1-stage 33-blade fan, 6-stage IP, 7-stage HP
Turbine: Single-stage HP, single-stage IP, 3-stage LP
Performance
Maximum thrust: 75.02 kN (7,650 kgf); (16,859 lbf)
Overall pressure ratio: 21.9 : 1
Turbine inlet temperature: 1,197 C (2,186 F)
Specific fuel consumption: 61 kg/kN/h (0.608 lb/lbf*hr)
Thrust-to-weight ratio: 5.6

Powerplant: 3 x Lotarev D-36 turbofan engines, 63.75 kN (14,330 lbf) thrust each.

Design and development.

The engine was developed for the Yak-42, An-72 and An-74 aircraft and was very advanced when it was first introduced in the 1970s. The engine was designed by Vladimir Lotarev. The first test runs began in 1971, first flight tests followed in 1974, serial production began in 1977.

The engine has a single-stage fan with 29 titanium blades and a Kevlar outer shell, which is driven by a three-stage turbine. The six-stage low pressure compressor with titanium blades is driven by a single-stage non-cooled low pressure turbine. The seven-stage high-pressure compressor with steel blades is driven by a steel bladed high-pressure turbine.

Since the tradition in the Soviet era was to gradually and continuously improve engines in serviceability, engines went from Series 1 to 3A (depending on the application). The Series 1 (used on Yak-42D) did not feature any reverse thrust system however, series 1A to 3A were fitted with bucket-type thrust reversers (used on An-72/An-74). The most recent upgrade (after the Soviet breakup) is Series 4A which has been in manufacture since 2002. Improvements included updated curved titanium blades and a built-in reverse thrust device. More advanced blade design along with proprietary wear-resistant and heat-protective coatings have resulted in improved specific fuel consumption (kg/h/kgf) dropping from 0.65 to 0.63. Specified service life has also improved exponentially to 40,000 hours.

Powerplant: 3 x Lotarev D-36 turbofan engines, 63.75 kN (14,330 lbf) thrust each.

Design and development.

The engine was developed for the Yak-42, An-72 and An-74 aircraft and was very advanced when it was first introduced in the 1970s. The engine was designed by Vladimir Lotarev. The first test runs began in 1971, first flight tests followed in 1974, serial production began in 1977.

The engine has a single-stage fan with 29 titanium blades and a Kevlar outer shell, which is driven by a three-stage turbine. The six-stage low pressure compressor with titanium blades is driven by a single-stage non-cooled low pressure turbine. The seven-stage high-pressure compressor with steel blades is driven by a steel bladed high-pressure turbine.

Since the tradition in the Soviet era was to gradually and continuously improve engines in serviceability, engines went from Series 1 to 3A (depending on the application). The Series 1 (used on Yak-42D) did not feature any reverse thrust system however, series 1A to 3A were fitted with bucket-type thrust reversers (used on An-72/An-74). The most recent upgrade (after the Soviet breakup) is Series 4A which has been in manufacture since 2002. Improvements included updated curved titanium blades and a built-in reverse thrust device. More advanced blade design along with proprietary wear-resistant and heat-protective coatings have resulted in improved specific fuel consumption (kg/h/kgf) dropping from 0.65 to 0.63. Specified service life has also improved exponentially to 40,000 hours.

Design and development.

The engine was developed for the Yak-42, An-72 and An-74 aircraft and was very advanced when it was first introduced in the 1970s. The engine was designed by Vladimir Lotarev. The first test runs began in 1971, first flight tests followed in 1974, serial production began in 1977.

The engine has a single-stage fan with 29 titanium blades and a Kevlar outer shell, which is driven by a three-stage turbine. The six-stage low pressure compressor with titanium blades is driven by a single-stage non-cooled low pressure turbine. The seven-stage high-pressure compressor with steel blades is driven by a steel bladed high-pressure turbine.

Since the tradition in the Soviet era was to gradually and continuously improve engines in serviceability, engines went from Series 1 to 3A (depending on the application). The Series 1 (used on Yak-42D) did not feature any reverse thrust system however, series 1A to 3A were fitted with bucket-type thrust reversers (used on An-72/An-74). The most recent upgrade (after the Soviet breakup) is Series 4A which has been in manufacture since 2002. Improvements included updated curved titanium blades and a built-in reverse thrust device. More advanced blade design along with proprietary wear-resistant and heat-protective coatings have resulted in improved specific fuel consumption (kg/h/kgf) dropping from 0.65 to 0.63. Specified service life has also improved exponentially to 40,000 hours.

Triebwerk 2 war am 10.03.2010 im overhaul und HSI. Hier betrgt die Restzeit bis zur nchsten HSI noch 1196 Stunden. Das Engine hat noch 2896 Stunden bis zum overhaul.

O EC 120 COLIBRI um helicptero monomotor leve e polivalente com capacidade para 4 passageiros e 1 piloto. Foi projetado de forma a oferecer uma grande flexibilidade de utilizao aos seus usurios.

Moderno, o COLIBRI o primeiro helicptero em sua categoria (1,7 T) equipado com sistema de alimentao de combustvel e assentos resistentes a impactos. O embarque dos passageiros extremamente facilitado, devido total abertura das portas da cabine e a amplos degraus de acesso. O embarque das bagagens tambm rpido, graas a duas portas e acesso ao bagageiro, sem equivalncia nesta categoria, podendo acomodar cinco malas grandes. Em voo, o COLIBRI surpreende pelo conforto, pela potncia do motor (ARRIUS 2F da TURBOMECA), pela excelente visibilidade e pelo nvel reduzido de vibrao. Seu baixo ndice de rudo externo (6,6 dba, inferior aos limites fixados pela OACI) deve-se em parte s caractersticas do rotor principal e do rotor traseiro Fenestron de ltima gerao. O EC 120 COLIBRI incorpora os principais requisitos exigidos pelos operadores: manuteno reduzida, baixo custo tcnico e preo de venda competitivo, alm de excelente desempenho.

O Helicptero AS350 B2 equipado com um motor Turbomeca Arriel 1D1com de 732 shp (546 kW) , tem um excelente histrico comprovado. A sua flexibilidade e baixo custo de aquisio fizeram-lhe um helicptero muito procurado capaz de executar uma ampla gama de misses, incluindo; transporte de passageiros, a execuo do trabalho, formao profissional, observao, combate a incndios e de direito areo, entre outros. Com a sua cabine espaosa e confortvel acomodar um piloto mais at 6 passageiros, o AS350 B2 especialmente apreciado por suas capacidades de transporte de passageiros para misses VIP, voos tursticos e tarefas de servio pblico. Alm disso, sua ampla cabine e vista panormica garante melhor visibilidade para passageiros e tripulao.

O AS350 B2 um excelente helicptero utilitrio capaz de transportar carga externa de mais de 1 tonelada (2.200 lbs). Graas sua elevada carga til, que bem adequado para todas as misses que requerem vrios tipos de equipamentos, incluindo; polcia, notcias de coleta, transporte mdico e de operaes de servios pblicos. Com um tempo muito curto reconfigurao (menos de uma hora), este helicptero mono turbina capaz de completar vrias misses com rapidez e eficincia.

Verkaufe einen Mini 500 Helikopter von Revolution der neuesten Bravo- Generation.
Die Bravo-Version zeichnet sich durch zahlreiche Neuerungen und Verbesserungen aus.
So besitzt er zB. die versrkten Blattansteuerungen , 4 pneumatische Kompensatoren im Landegestell , Zuatsverstrebungen , ein Getrenntschmiersystem fr das Zweitacktgemisch des Rotax 582, eine verbesserte Motorabluftfhrung des Khlsystems und weiteres.Die Fliehkraftkupplung war ebenfalls zu schwach dimensioniert und wurde mit dem Antrieb fest verbunden.
An beiden Steuerhebeln ( Zyklisch Pitch ) sind einstellbare Schwingungsdmpfer verbaut.
Der Bausatz wurde kurz vor 2000 von Rotorway USA in die Niederlande ausgeliefert. 
Der Erstbesitzer hatte den Heli zirka 2002 startbereit. 
Seit der Fertigstellung wurde der Heli nur ein paar mal aus der beheitzten Halle geholt und laufen gelassen. Der Wunsch nach einer Helikopterpilotenlizenz ging durch Ermangelung an Zeit und Gesundheit nicht in Erfllung.
Ich hab den Heli mitte 2019 erworben und in monatelanger Arbeit fast jede Schraube und alle Verbindungen geprft !
Blattanstellwinkel wurden korrigiert , Vergaser gereinigt, Anlasserhalterung verstrkt, altes Zweitaktl sowie Kraftstoff und einige Leitungen ersetzt.
Der Heli hat jetzt 3 Std ( Probelufe und ein kurzer Schwebeflug ) auf der Uhr. 
Hier noch einige technische Daten.
V-Max 193 Kmh , Reisegeschwindigkeit 120 Kmh , Lnge 6,8 m Hhe 2,7 m , Breite 1,6 m , Tankinhalt 57 L , Reichweite 3 Std. ,Steigleistung 5,6 m/s ,Dienstgipfelhhe 3000 m , Hauptrotor 5,85 m - Blatttiefe 20 cm , Heckrotor1,17 m - Blatttiefe 10 cm , Leergewicht 220 Kg , Zuladung 161 Kg ,max. Abflugmasse 381 Kg , Motor Rotax 582 2-Zylinder Zweitakt 65 PS mit Wasserkhlung -Zwangslftung und Doppelzndanlage.
Die Kraftbertragung erfolgt vom Motor ber einen breiten Zahnriemen zum Hauptrotorgetriebe und ber Kardan zum Heckrotorgetriebe.
Der Sitz ist nach vorn und hinten auf die Grsse des Piloten einstellbar. In der Kabiene ist es erstaunlich gerumig und auch fr grssere und breitere Piloten bequem. Das einsteigen gestaltet sich sehr unproblematisch. Mein vorheriger Heli ( Rotorway 162 F ) war dagegen wesentlich beengter.
Die Rotorbltter sind aus GFK gefertigt.
Motor kann bei Besichtigung laufen - und alle Agregate drehen gelassen werden.
Eine Kiste mit umfangreichen Dokumenten sowie eine Transportbox fr die Hauptrotorbltter sind auch dabei. Der Bau wurde mit sehr vielen Fotos dokumentiert !
Eine Lieferung im Umkreis von zirka 300 Km whre nach vorheriger Anzahlung gegen Unkostenbeitrag mglich.
Sie haben nun die Mglichkeit einen neuwertigen Helikopter zu einem gnstigen Preis zu erwerben !!
Verkauft wird unter Ausschluss jeglicher Gewhrleistung und ohne Rckgaberecht da Privatverkauf.

Para otimizar a interface homem-mquina, o helicptero est basicamente equipado com o VEMD (Vehicle and Engine Multifunction Display) no painel de instrumentos: uma nova gerao de instrumentao integrada que permite ao piloto ver todos os principais parmetros do helicptero e do motor de uma s vez em uma tela LCD dupla. O AS350 B3 alimentado com um motor TURBOMECA ARRIEL 2 de 847 shp (632 kW) e equipado com um sistema FADEC de canal duplo (Full Authority Digital Engine Control.) Este motor o torna perfeitamente adequado para operao em condies tais como reas montanhosas, elevadas, reas quentes e secas. Com uma capacidade de carga inferior a 1.400 kg (3.086 lb) e uma alta razo de subida, este helicptero a ferramenta ideal para transportar cargas pesadas e realizar operaes de explorao madeireira nas montanhas. Quando equipado com trem de pouso de baixa descida, a velocidade mxima de cruzeiro de 140 kts. Esta alta performance em combinao com a sua elevada capacidade de gancho torna o AS350 B3 uma aeronave muito procurada para transporte de passageiros ou operaes de utilidade.

O helicptero Bell 407GX o primeiro monoturbina do mundo a contar com painel digital com caractersticas daqueles presentes em grandes jatos. A aeronave alcana velocidade mxima de 246 km/h e pode percorrer at 611 km sem necessidade de reabastecimento. O Bell 407GX leva at sete ocupantes e sua maior vantagem poder levantar voo lotado e com tanque cheio j que ainda assim estar dentro da capacidade mxima de decolagem.

O Helicptero Robinson R44 Raven II de alta performance , possui um sistema de rotor de ps, cclico com T e um motor Lycoming IO-540 com injeo direta. O Motor Lycoming IO-540 possui melhor performance em altitude, maior capacidade de potncia, eliminando a necessidade de um carburador.

O desenho de cabine aberta da Robinson permite uma viso desobstruda de qualquer assento. Sua fuselagem leve e aerodinmica resulta em maior velocidade e economia de combustvel. O rotor de cauda foi desenvolvido para reduzir o rudo emitido no sobrevoo do helicptero.

The Klimov TV3-117 is a Russian gas turbine aero engine. It is used in most medium lift, utility, and attack helicopters designed by the Mil and Kamov design bureaus. The TV3-117 turboshaft engine was developed in 1974. Later the Klimov TV3-117 was installed on 95% of all helicopters designed by Mil and Kamov Engineering Centre. The engine has been produced in many variants.

("VM" stands for "high altitude, modernized") for Mi-28 helicopters and later installed also on Mi-8MT/Mi-171 models. This engine features an automatic switch to emergency power. It was awarded type certificates by the IAC Aviation Registry, India, the Republic of China and the People's Republic of China. Mass-produced since 1986

The Klimov TV3-117 is a Russian gas turbine aero engine. It is used in most medium lift, utility, and attack helicopters designed by the Mil and Kamov design bureaus. The TV3-117 turboshaft engine was developed in 1974. Later the Klimov TV3-117 was installed on 95% of all helicopters designed by Mil and Kamov Engineering Centre. The engine has been produced in many variants.

("VM" stands for "high altitude, modernized") for Mi-28 helicopters and later installed also on Mi-8MT/Mi-171 models. This engine features an automatic switch to emergency power. It was awarded type certificates by the IAC Aviation Registry, India, the Republic of China and the People's Republic of China. Mass-produced since 1986

- The firefighting Ka‐32A11BC helicopter boasts over 40 different options for firefighting equipment including the Bambi‐Bucket and Simplex systems, and water cannon for horizontal firefighting. It can fight fires in heavy smoke, on the upper floors of high‐rise buildings, and on oil and gas industry facilities. The Ka‐32A11BC is recognised by experts as one of the finest firefighting helicopters in the world, and is a symbol of the Global Helicopter Firefighting Initiative, a programme aimed at increasing the efficiency of specialised firefighting helicopters kitted out with suspended fire‐fighting systems, water cannons and other fire‐fighting equipment.
- The Ka‐32A11BC is indispensable in complex construction works, due to the absence of a tail rotor, its precision hover ability, great manoeuvrability and carrying capacity.
- The search and rescue Ka‐32A11BC inherited the best features from the naval ship‐based Ka‐27PS, which formed the basis for its design. It can operate in very damp conditions and displays great resilience to the aggressive marine environment. The Ka‐32A11BCs particular design enables it to fly in high turbulence and stormy conditions, making it ideally suited to carrying out search and rescue operations in critical situations.
- The Ka‐32A11BC can be equipped with a medical module comprising the latest intensive care equipment. Thanks to this, resuscitation and life support can be performed in‐flight, when it is being used to transport the sick and injured.
- In supporting the police and special forces, the Ka‐32A11BC can be fitted with modern surveillance equipment, tracking and loudhailer communications, and can be used to transport a landing force. Its high‐precision hover capacity and maneuverability make it more effective in urban situations.
The Ansat is powered by PW 207K Pratt & Whitney Canada 630 h.p. engines and FADEC system that ensures the helicopter can continue to fly if one engine fails.

O helicptero Robinson R44 Raven II de alta performance , possui um sistema de rotor de ps, cclico com T e um motor Lycoming IO-540 com injeo direta. O Motor Lycoming IO-540 possui melhor performance em altitude, maior capacidade de potncia, eliminando a necessidade de um carburador.

O Helicptero Robinson R44 Raven II de alta performance , possui um sistema de rotor de ps, cclico com T e um motor Lycoming IO-540 com injeo direta. O Motor Lycoming IO-540 possui melhor performance em altitude, maior capacidade de potncia, eliminando a necessidade de um carburador.

O desenho de cabine aberta da Robinson permite uma viso desobstruda de qualquer assento. Sua fuselagem leve e aerodinmica resulta em maior velocidade e economia de combustvel. O rotor de cauda foi desenvolvido para reduzir o rudo emitido no sobrevoo do helicptero.

O EC 120 COLIBRI um helicptero monomotor leve e polivalente com capacidade para 4 passageiros e 1 piloto. Foi projetado de forma a oferecer uma grande flexibilidade de utilizao aos seus usurios.

Moderno, o COLIBRI o primeiro helicptero em sua categoria (1,7 T) equipado com sistema de alimentao de combustvel e assentos resistentes a impactos. O embarque dos passageiros extremamente facilitado, devido total abertura das portas da cabine e a amplos degraus de acesso. O embarque das bagagens tambm rpido, graas a duas portas e acesso ao bagageiro, sem equivalncia nesta categoria, podendo acomodar cinco malas grandes. Em voo, o COLIBRI surpreende pelo conforto, pela potncia do motor (ARRIUS 2F da TURBOMECA), pela excelente visibilidade e pelo nvel reduzido de vibrao. Seu baixo ndice de rudo externo (6,6 dba, inferior aos limites fixados pela OACI) deve-se em parte s caractersticas do rotor principal e do rotor traseiro Fenestron de ltima gerao. O EC 120 COLIBRI incorpora os principais requisitos exigidos pelos operadores: manuteno reduzida, baixo custo tcnico e preo de venda competitivo, alm de excelente desempenho.

O Bell Jet Ranger 206B-III um dos helicpteros mais conhecidos de todos os tempos. Este helicptero mono turbina provou-se como uma plataforma confivel e verstil para fins comerciais, de servios pblicos e de transporte de passageiros.
Capaz de acomodar um piloto e at 4 passageiros com uma excelente vista do ambiente externo.
O helicptero Jet Ranger possui autonomia de mais 3 horas de voo, e uma velocidade de cruzeiro em torno de 130 kts.

Sem ar condicionado.

The Robinson R66 Turbine is a five-seat helicopter, incorporating many features of the R44 with the enhancement of a fifth seat and a very large baggage compartment.
The RR300 turbine engine delivers increased performance in terms of reserve power, altitude performance and speed.
Popular Robinson R44 options such as HID landing lights, leather seats, and a stereo audio control panel, are all standard on the R66 Turbine. Optional equipment includes the Garmin G500H Primary Flight Display and Multifunction Display (PFD/MFD) and the HeliSAS autopilot.
The Robinson R66 Turbine is also available as a Turbine Marine with fixed or pop-out floats. Contact Sloane to discuss R66 helicopter options tailored to your requirements.

The Robinson R44 Raven II is the worlds top-selling helicopter. It has a fuel-injected Lycoming engine delivering incomparable power, speed and altitude performance in a compact, comfortable and cost-effective helicopter.
The aircraft is also available as an IFR Trainer, Newscopter, Police helicopter and Clipper II with either pop-out or utility floats. Contact Sloane to discuss R44 helicopter options tailored to your requirements.

The Robinson R44 Raven I provides high quality and cost-effectiveness, delivering the performance of a turbine helicopter at an affordable piston helicopter price. The tried and tested Lycoming engine is renowned worldwide for long-life and reliability.
The R44 Raven I offers precision-engineered power, high reliability, fuel economy, endurance and remarkable altitude performance, payload and speed. Optional equipment includes the HeliSAS autopilot.
The R44 Raven I is also available as a Clipper I equipped with fixed utility floats for over water operations. Contact Sloane to discuss R44 helicopter options tailored to your requirements.

O helicptero Robinson R44 Raven II de alta performance , possui um sistema de rotor de ps, cclico com T e um motor Lycoming IO-540 com injeo direta. O Motor Lycoming IO-540 possui melhor performance em altitude, maior capacidade de potncia, eliminando a necessidade de um carburador.O desenho de cabine aberta da Robinson permite uma viso desobstruda de qualquer assento. Sua fuselagem leve e aerodinmica resulta em maior velocidade e economia de combustvel. O rotor de cauda foi desenvolvido para reduzir o rudo emitido no sobrevo do helicptero.
